00:00:14:050000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:14:050000.Dialogue: So, do you find the weather satisfying? Are you currently sharing in the triumph of some local sports team?

00:00:21:100000.Speaker: Penny
00:00:21:100000.Dialogue: What's wrong with you? You're freaking me out.

00:00:24:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:24:100000.Dialogue: I'm striking up a casual conversation with you. S'up?

00:00:35:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:35:230000.Dialogue: All right, but I'm given to understand that when you have something awkward to discuss with someone, it's more palatable to preface it with banal chit chat.

00:00:44:130000.Speaker: Penny
00:00:44:130000.Dialogue: So, this wasn't the awkward part?

00:00:58:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:58:030000.Dialogue: Oh, good, I used that right.

00:01:01:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:01:030000.Dialogue: Anyway, you're aware that Leonard has entered into a new romantic relationship which includes a sexual component?

00:01:14:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:14:120000.Dialogue: Her name is Dr. Stephanie Barnett and she is a highly distinguished surgical resident at Freemont Memorial.

00:01:28:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:28:170000.Dialogue: See, of the handful of women Leonard's been involved with, she's the only one I have ever found tolerable.

00:01:47:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:47:180000.Dialogue: Anyway, should you have any interaction with her, it would be most helpful that she not see you as a sexual rival.

00:01:56:040000.Speaker: Penny
00:01:56:040000.Dialogue: Yeah, I think she's pretty safe.

00:01:58:200000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:58:200000.Dialogue: You say that now, but consider the following scenario: You're sitting in your apartment, it's late, you're alone. Your hypothalamus is swimming in a soup of estrogen and progesterone

00:02:09:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:02:09:090000.Dialogue: and suddenly even Leonard seems like a viable sexual candidate.

00:02:15:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:02:15:210000.Dialogue: Or a hookup as it's referred to by today's urban youth.

00:02:37:220000.Speaker: Penny
00:02:37:220000.Dialogue: Always nice talking to you, Sheldon.

00:03:23:110000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:23:110000.Dialogue: And you said there'd never be enough pasta for the three of us.

00:03:28:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:28:230000.Dialogue: You know, Italian housewives have a rule of thumb. A handful of dry pasta about an inch in diameter is sufficient for each person as it doubles in volume when cooked.

00:03:41:200000.Speaker: Leonard
00:03:41:200000.Dialogue: She doesn't mean it. She's just being nice.

00:03:46:190000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:46:190000.Dialogue: Well, since Leonard seems to be dropping the conversational ball, I guess I'll just have to pick it up.

00:04:00:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:00:060000.Dialogue: Have you ever witnessed a violent crime?

00:04:11:140000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:11:140000.Dialogue: Technically not a fruit, but all right.

00:04:15:220000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:15:220000.Dialogue: Where did you do your medical internship?

00:04:20:110000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:20:110000.Dialogue: Really? That's where I was born!

00:04:26:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:26:120000.Dialogue: I spent so much of my childhood at that hospital. When I was 12, I got to ride there in a helicopter.

00:04:36:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:36:180000.Dialogue: A little mishap while I was building my own CAT scanner.

00:04:40:070000.Speaker: Steph
00:04:40:070000.Dialogue: I'm sorry, you tried to build your own CAT scanner?

00:04:43:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:43:060000.Dialogue: No, I didn't try, I succeeded. In fact, I was briefly able to see the inside of my sister's guinea pig, Snowball, before he caught fire.

00:04:51:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:51:230000.Dialogue: It led to an interesting expression in our house: Not a Snowball's chance in a CAT scanner.

00:05:01:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:01:130000.Dialogue: Excuse me. When I come back, just for fun, the subject will be alternative history. Specifically, how would the Civil War have gone differently if Lincoln had been a robot sent from the future?

00:05:17:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:17:210000.Dialogue: Look at that, there's even pasta left over.

00:05:21:090000.Speaker: Leonard
00:05:21:090000.Dialogue: Do you understand that this was supposed to be a date?

00:05:24:040000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:24:040000.Dialogue: I do. Do you? Because frankly, you've been in a foul mood since I sat down.

00:05:32:130000.Speaker: Leonard
00:05:32:130000.Dialogue: Okay, here's my question. Why did you sit down?

00:05:37:150000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:37:150000.Dialogue: To help. Look, if you fail at this relationship, and history suggests you will,

00:05:44:040000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:44:040000.Dialogue: then we risk losing the medical officer that our landing party has always needed.

00:05:54:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:54:170000.Dialogue: You're Kirk, I'm Spock, Wolowitz is Scotty, Koothrappali is the guy who always gets killed...

00:06:12:040000.Speaker: Steph
00:06:12:040000.Dialogue: So, we're all standing around looking at the post-op X ray and there it is, clear as day, right in the guy's chest cavity... one of my earrings.

00:06:22:010000.Speaker: Leonard
00:06:22:010000.Dialogue: Oh, my God, what did you do?

00:06:24:230000.Speaker: Steph
00:06:24:230000.Dialogue: What do you think I did? I discreetly slipped off the other earring, put it in my pocket and then got the hell out of there!

00:06:32:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:32:130000.Dialogue: I have a bone to pick with you, sir.

00:06:37:160000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:37:160000.Dialogue: Hi, Stephanie. I'm sorry I'm late, but your companion left the most indecipherable invitation.

00:06:46:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:46:100000.Dialogue: We're going to the movies. What movie? What theater? What time?

00:06:52:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:52:170000.Dialogue: If you were trying to make it impossible to locate you, you couldn't have done a better job.

00:07:00:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:00:120000.Dialogue: It took me nearly 20 minutes to browse the history on your computer to see what movie times you looked up.

00:07:06:220000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:06:220000.Dialogue: Wait here, I'll find us seats.

00:07:23:220000.Speaker: Leonard
00:07:23:220000.Dialogue: He's finding the acoustic sweet spot.

00:07:32:120000.Speaker: Leonard
00:07:32:120000.Dialogue: Sometimes he brings a toy xylophone.

00:07:42:040000.Speaker: Leonard
00:07:42:040000.Dialogue: I am really sorry about this.

00:07:44:090000.Speaker: Steph
00:07:44:090000.Dialogue: No, it's fine. You know, he's sweet.

00:07:54:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:54:180000.Dialogue: My apologies, you've been sitting in it all along. - You want to slide over one?

00:08:25:190000.Speaker: Leonard
00:08:25:190000.Dialogue: What, Sheldon? What, Sheldon?! What, Sheldon?!

00:08:30:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:08:30:020000.Dialogue: Tell me what you see here.

00:08:31:200000.Speaker: Leonard
00:08:31:200000.Dialogue: The blunt instrument that will be the focus of my murder trial?

00:08:35:200000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:08:35:200000.Dialogue: This is Stephanie's Facebook page. Now, where it should say in a relationship, what does it say?

00:08:42:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:08:42:180000.Dialogue: Furthermore, earlier this evening, she threw a digital sheep at some guy named Mike.

00:08:50:050000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:08:50:050000.Dialogue: Who's Mike?! Why does he get a digital sheep and not you?

00:08:54:080000.Speaker: Leonard
00:08:54:080000.Dialogue: It's just her Facebook page and we've only been going out a couple of weeks.

00:08:58:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:08:58:130000.Dialogue: You don't see it, do you? We're losing her.

00:09:04:210000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:04:210000.Dialogue: I'm going to make this very simple for you. You are not in this relationship.

00:09:11:040000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:11:040000.Dialogue: I am. Ergo, you have no say in anything that happens between me and Stephanie.

00:09:21:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:09:21:230000.Dialogue: I'm afraid I can't allow that. Pursuant to Starfleet General Order 104, Section A: You are deemed unfit and I hereby relieve you of your command.

00:09:34:010000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:34:010000.Dialogue: General Order 104, Section A does not apply in this situation.

00:09:37:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:09:37:060000.Dialogue: - Give me one good reason why not.

00:10:01:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:01:120000.Dialogue: It's my understanding that an unsolicited gift of food can be a precursor to an impromptu invitation to come in and chat.

00:10:11:100000.Speaker: Penny
00:10:11:100000.Dialogue: Would you like to come in?

00:10:13:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:13:060000.Dialogue: I suppose I could spare a few minutes.

00:10:29:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:29:090000.Dialogue: I'm certain this will come as no surprise to you, but Leonard is failing in yet another relationship.

00:10:58:200000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:58:200000.Dialogue: So, what is the down and the low? And don't worry, this is all entirely confidential, so, you feel free to include any and all shortcomings in the bedroom.

00:11:08:070000.Speaker: Penny
00:11:08:070000.Dialogue: We never got to the bedroom.

00:11:15:060000.Speaker: Penny
00:11:15:060000.Dialogue: All right, you know what? I'll tell you what happened. We were young, we were very much in love, but we could only communicate through a time-traveling mailbox at my lake house.

00:11:32:140000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:32:140000.Dialogue: It's not enough that you made me watch that movie, but now you mock me with it?

00:11:39:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:39:230000.Dialogue: Gentlemen, I have a question about dating and relationships.

00:11:50:080000.Speaker: Raj
00:11:50:080000.Dialogue: You told me you were going to have the talk with him.

00:11:54:030000.Speaker: Howard
00:11:54:030000.Dialogue: I've been waiting for someone to have the talk with me.

00:11:57:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:57:170000.Dialogue: More to the point, it's about finding a way to keep Leonard and Stephanie together.

00:12:04:030000.Speaker: Howard
00:12:04:030000.Dialogue: Look at Leonard's record. 27 days with Joyce Kim.

00:12:07:070000.Speaker: Raj
00:12:07:070000.Dialogue: During which she defected to North Korea.

00:12:11:040000.Speaker: Howard
00:12:11:040000.Dialogue: Two booty calls with Leslie Winkle.

00:12:13:040000.Speaker: Raj
00:12:13:040000.Dialogue: For which she awarded him the nickname Speed of Light Leonard.

00:12:17:130000.Speaker: Raj
00:12:17:130000.Dialogue: - Which would have been two and a half if they ordered the souffle when they sat down.

00:12:23:200000.Speaker: Howard
00:12:23:200000.Dialogue: Based on the geometric progression, his relationship with Stephanie should have ended after 20 minutes.

00:12:29:050000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:29:050000.Dialogue: Yes, I'm aware of the math. Y equals 27 days over 12 to the nth. The issue remains. How do we circumvent his inevitable rejection?

00:12:38:140000.Speaker: Raj
00:12:38:140000.Dialogue: If you want to guarantee his appeal to Stephanie, your best bet would be to kill all the other men on the planet.

00:12:46:040000.Speaker: Howard
00:12:46:040000.Dialogue: Here's what you shouldn't do. Don't shpritz him with that body spray from the commercial where the women undress when they smell it. That doesn't work at all.

00:12:56:100000.Speaker: Howard
00:12:56:100000.Dialogue: No matter how much you put on.

00:13:00:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:00:020000.Dialogue: That's all you've got? Apocalyptic genocide and go easy on the cologne?

00:13:32:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:32:230000.Dialogue: I see. Apparently, my earlier inquiry regarding you and Leonard crossed some sort of line. I apologize.

00:13:42:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:42:120000.Dialogue: Have you and I returned to a social equilibrium?

00:13:54:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:54:170000.Dialogue: I've been doing some research online, and apparently, female primates, you know, apes, chimpanzees, you...

00:14:02:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:02:070000.Dialogue: They find their mate more desirable when he's courted by another female. Now, this effect is intensified when the rival female is secreting the pheromones associated with ovulation. Which brings me back to my question. Where are you...

00:14:22:120000.Speaker: Leonard
00:14:22:120000.Dialogue: All I'm saying is if they can cure yellow fever and malaria, why can't they do something about lactose intolerance?

00:14:30:200000.Speaker: Steph
00:14:30:200000.Dialogue: Leonard, you're going to have to let this go. You had a little cheese dip, you farted. I thought it was cute.

00:15:00:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:00:230000.Dialogue: I have a craving for white asparagus that apparently is destined to go unsatisfied.

00:15:21:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:21:100000.Dialogue: When I fail to open this jar and you succeed, it will establish you as the alpha male. You see... when a female witnesses an exhibition of physical domination, she produces the hormone oxytocin. If the two of you then engage in intercourse, this will create the biochemical reaction in the brain which lay people naively interpret as falling in love.

00:15:44:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:15:44:020000.Dialogue: Would it work if I just punched you in the face?

00:15:48:040000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:48:040000.Dialogue: Yes, actually it would, but let's see how the lid goes.

00:15:51:220000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:51:220000.Dialogue: I'm not strong enough, Leonard, you'll have to do it.

00:16:13:140000.Speaker: Steph
00:16:13:140000.Dialogue: You want some help with that?

00:16:19:110000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:19:110000.Dialogue: He's got it, and that's not surprising. It's something I long ago came to peace with in my role as the beta male.

00:16:42:200000.Speaker: Steph
00:16:42:200000.Dialogue: - Honey, you're going to need stitches.

00:16:46:180000.Speaker: Steph
00:16:46:180000.Dialogue: Well, yeah, I mean, just a few.

00:17:02:110000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:02:110000.Dialogue: FYI, I was defrosting a steak in there.

00:17:09:080000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:09:080000.Dialogue: What a beautiful job Stephanie did. I might have gone with a mattress suture instead of a blanket stitch, but you can't argue with her results. It's a shame it won't scar. The war wound is a time-honored badge of masculinity.

00:17:24:200000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:24:200000.Dialogue: I can't remember a time when you weren't talking.

00:17:29:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:29:060000.Dialogue: Just for the record, my efforts to establish you as the alpha male were not aided by you bursting into tears.

00:17:34:140000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:34:140000.Dialogue: I did not burst into tears, my eyes just got a little watery.

00:17:39:190000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:39:190000.Dialogue: She stuck a needle into my hand!

00:17:43:130000.Speaker: Steph
00:17:43:130000.Dialogue: Hey, how's my big cry baby?

00:17:49:110000.Speaker: Steph
00:17:49:110000.Dialogue: I'm just teasing you. But, yeah, you did.

00:17:53:230000.Speaker: Steph
00:17:53:230000.Dialogue: It's all good. What do you say we get you home and put you to bed?

00:17:57:080000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:57:080000.Dialogue: Are you still going to spend the night?

00:17:59:190000.Speaker: Steph
00:17:59:190000.Dialogue: No, I think that you probably need to rest.

00:18:01:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:18:01:230000.Dialogue: She's right. As long as you're vomiting, coitus is contra-indicated.

00:18:14:210000.Speaker: Steph
00:18:14:210000.Dialogue: Okay, I'm going to go get your discharge papers.

00:18:22:050000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:18:22:050000.Dialogue: You seem like a perfectly pleasant person. I can't understand why women have such a hard time loving you.

00:18:34:150000.Speaker: Leonard
00:18:34:150000.Dialogue: Can you open this for me?

00:18:44:200000.Speaker: Raj
00:18:44:200000.Dialogue: Answering the question once and for all why Wolowitz bailed out of medical school.

00:18:52:190000.Speaker: Penny
00:18:52:190000.Dialogue: Your Facebook status update. Leonard Hofstadter is in a relationship.

00:19:00:130000.Speaker: Howard
00:19:00:130000.Dialogue: Oh, man, did you switch your status before she did?

00:19:05:120000.Speaker: Howard
00:19:05:120000.Dialogue: Speaking as an expert, way to look needy.

00:19:09:130000.Speaker: Penny
00:19:09:130000.Dialogue: Seriously? You went first, after only two weeks? That's bold...

00:19:14:090000.Speaker: Leonard
00:19:14:090000.Dialogue: It's not bold, it's a mistake. I didn't change my status.

00:19:24:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:19:24:180000.Dialogue: I had no choice. He cried in front of her.

00:19:31:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:19:31:230000.Dialogue: It's hardly hacking when you use the same password for everything, Kal-El.

00:19:37:230000.Speaker: Leonard
00:19:37:230000.Dialogue: Are you insane? Now she's going to think I'm desperate. You've destroyed this relationship! And you know what the worst part is? You don't even understand what you did wrong because you can't conceive of something that you are not an expert in!

00:19:51:200000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:19:51:200000.Dialogue: - In which I am not an expert.

00:19:57:170000.Speaker: Leonard
00:19:57:170000.Dialogue: I don't want to hear another word out of you.

00:20:03:100000.Speaker: Penny
00:20:03:100000.Dialogue: What's wrong, Lassie? Timmy fall down the well?

00:20:11:020000.Speaker: Penny
00:20:11:020000.Dialogue: She just updated her Facebook status.

00:20:13:160000.Speaker: Howard
00:20:13:160000.Dialogue: Stephanie Barnett is in a relationship with Leonard Hofstadter.

00:20:23:040000.Speaker: Leonard
00:20:23:040000.Dialogue: Look at that. I have a girlfriend.

00:20:27:040000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:20:27:040000.Dialogue: If I am permitted to speak again, Dr. Sheldon Cooper for the win.
